b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Devin is best suited for teams wanting autonomous coding agents, complex multi step tasks, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Sourcegraph Cody, meanwhile, shines for large codebases, teams needing codebase wide context, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, Devin describes itself as \"The first fully autonomous AI software engineer.\" Sourcegraph Cody, established in 2023, positions itself as \"AI that understands your entire codebase.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Sourcegraph Cody** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (9 vs 8), more competitive pricing, availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Devin is a poor choice — far from it. Devin excels in its own right, particularly for teams wanting autonomous coding agents and complex multi step tasks.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value deep codebase understanding, go with Sourcegraph Cody. If can work autonomously on tasks matters more to you, Devin is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
